@node "Usage" "Usage"
 USAGE:

 SIMPLE! Just Run 'Life' as a cli exe with the node number as a argument.
 i.e.

 Life 1 - Node 1
 Life 99 - Node 99


 This also works on other amiga software bbs's that are paragon compatible.
 It has been tested on System-X successfully running a paragon door =)
 
 It may work on others, i dont know, let me know if ya try it.

 To use it, all yya do is, when a node/door locks up then in the background
 just run 'Life (NODE)'  (e.g. Life 1) and it should uncrash, sometimes it
may
 take a few attempts, i don't know why and i don't really care, it works.

 This will then end the crashed door and return you back to the bbs/menu it
 was called from, if theres a problem and it can't be returned to the
 system then it will simply unhang the door then TWIT (logoff) and return
 the bbs to 'Wait for caller' mode.

 NOTE /X\2 USERS (Maxs Pro 2):
 
 This door was written before /X\2 came about so it still works but
 slightly differently, due to the paragon door handler rewrite (see /X\2
 dox) you may need to run the utils as node (number)+node(number) e.g.

 If node 1 locks then you may need to run 'Life 2' 
 I probably could fix this but its simpler to just change the argument.

 You can run this utility as many times as ya want to uncrash the door(s)
 sometimes it may take a few times.. but it has never done me any harm by
 doing so, it's up to you tho.. remember read the @{"DISCLAIMER" link "Disclaimer" 0}!    

 PLEASE NOTE:

 Don't be sending me emails saying it dont work, this utility has worked
 for me AT LEAST 95% of the time, the only time it won't work is then the
 crash is due to a DOS fault and not a bbs function (i.e. writing a file)
  
@endnode

